 :macrology: /mak·rol'@·jee/, n. 1. Set of usually complex or crufty macros,
e.g., as part of a large system written in {LISP}, {TECO}, or (less commonly)
assembler. 2. The art and science involved in comprehending a macrology in
sense 1. Sometimes studying the macrology of a system is not unlike
archeology, ecology, or {theology}, hence the sound-alike construction. see
also {boxology}.